KRISHNA BUS SERVICE LTD. V. SMT. MANGLI & ORS [1976] INSC 8; AIR 1976 SC 700; 1976 (3) SCR 178; 1976 (1) SCC 793 (21 January 1976)

 SARKARIA, RANJIT SINGH SARKARIA, RANJIT SINGH FAZALALI, SYED MURTAZA 
CITATION: 1976 AIR 700 1976 SCR (3) 178 1976 SCC (1) 793 
ACT:
 Negligence-Vicarious responsibility of the management in fatal injury cases-Presumption when arises-Liability is on both the rash and negligent driver and the management since the driver acted "in the course of its employment".
 Duty to care-Absence of explanation by the defendants affords reasonable evidence towards contributory negligence.
 Maxim-Res ipsa loquitur-Applies to fatal accident cases on road.
 Second appeal-Reappraisal of evidence on record by Supreme Court only in exceptional cases where injustice would result.
 
